  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN319-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. ālaṅkuṭi vaṅkaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN319">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>pūvaṟ paṭuviṟ kūvaṟ ṟōṇṭiya</l>
<l>ceṅkaṭ ciṉṉīrpeyta cīṟil</l>
<l>muṉṟi lirunta mutuvāyc cāṭi</l>
<l>yāṅkaḵ ṭuṇṭeṉa vaṟitumā ciṉṟu</l>
<l>paṭalai muṉṟiṟ ciṟutiṉai yuṇaṅkal</l>
<l>puṟavu mītalu maṟavu muṇkeṉap</l>
<l>peytaṟ kelliṉṟu poḻutē yataṉāl</l>
<l>muyalcuṭṭa vāyiṉun tarukuvēm pukutan</l>
<l>tīṅkirun  tīmō mutuvāyp pāṇa</l>
<l>koṭuṅkōṭ  ṭāmā ṉaṭuṅkutalaik kuḻavi</l>
<l>puṉṟalaic ciṟāar kaṉṟeṉap pūṭṭuñ</l>
<l>cīṟūr maṉṉa ṉerunai ñāṅkar</l>
<l>vēntuviṭu toḻiloṭu ceṉṟaṉaṉ vantuniṉ</l>
<l>pāṭiṉi mālai yaṇiya</l>
<l>vāṭāt tāmarai cūṭṭuva ṉiṉakkē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The jar with a frayed opening that was in the front yard</l>
<l>of the little house into which a little red-soiled water had been poured</l>
<l>when a hollow had been made in the well of red soil,</l>
<l>since there it has been drunk to the bottom, it is empty. There is no blame.</l>
<l>The time is without light for strewing </l>
<l>dried grains of little millet in the shaded front yard</l>
<l>thinking “let the doves and partridges eat [it] completely.” Therefore,</l>
<l>We shall give [you] hare, even if it is [only] roasted [pieces]. Enter</l>
<l>[and] sit here, bard with old truth!</l>
<l>Yesterday here the lord of the little village,</l>
<l>where ruddy-haired boys fasten as a [house] calf</l>
<l>the calf with trembling head of the wild cow with curved horns,</l>
<l>has gone with a task set by the king. Coming back</l>
<l>he will put on you an unfading lotus,</l>
<l>while your songstress will be adorned with a garland.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="4b">
<l>we will know that there is [some] on the bottom there.</l>
</lg>
</lg>


